Prophylaxis of hepatic insufficiency after major hepatic resections
The article deals with a problem of prophylaxis of hepatic insufficiency in oncological patients after liver resections. We analyzed data of effectiveness and safety of the use of Remaxol in oncological patients with hepatic metastasis of colorectal cancer--dynamics of indicators of cytolysis and cholestasis, hepatic protein synthesis, exchange of pigments, pro- and antioxidant system and the level of endogen intoxication in postoperative period. Use of Remaxol allows decreasing the duration of postoperative rehabilitation and intensive care unit staying. 